      • asString

        public static java.lang.String asString(java.lang.String message,
                                        java.lang.Throwable e)
        Like asString(Throwable), but prints the message argument first. The exception message (and stack trace) associated are always printed.
        Parameters:
        message - Message about the throwable.
        e - Throwable
        Returns:
        String containing the message and the printed stack trace.

      • addStackTrace

        public static java.lang.StringBuffer addStackTrace(java.lang.StringBuffer b,
                                                   java.lang.StackTraceElement[] stackTrace)
        Add the stack trace (one element per line) to the indicated string buffer. You can get the stack trace from an Exception with e.getStackTrace().
        Parameters:
        b - add the stack trace to this string buffer.
        stackTrace - Array of Stack Trace Elements.
        Returns:
        the modified StringBuffer (the b argument).
